<section id="analyzing-gps-walking-data-from-phyphox" class="level1">
<h1>Analyzing GPS Walking Data from Phyphox</h1>
<section id="gps-safety" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="gps-safety">GPS Safety</h2>
<p>GPS data sets have precise <strong>longitude</strong> and <strong>latitude</strong> values. Share raw data cautiously to avoid leaking private data. (<em>note: this is also useful for geometry. The earth can be seen as a sphere and this data can be converted spherical coordinates</em>)</p>
</section>
<section id="data-source" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="data-source">Data Source</h2>
<p>In this set I am in a public place and recording a <strong>~6 minute</strong> walk that is not anywhere near my home.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb10" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb10-1"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"># show a data sample</span></span>
<span id="cb10-2"><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">glimpse</span>(walk)</span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="cell-output cell-output-stdout">
<pre><code>Rows: 463
Columns: 11
$ `Time (s)`                &lt;dbl&gt; 0.006688125, 2.309468384, 3.308960415, 4.309…
